        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"224323\">Junyan Xu</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/field.20extension.20tower/near/535799169\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>It can't be an instance because the goal doesn't contain F. It could be if F_bar is replaced by <code>AlgebraicClosure F</code>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>thanks! And do you have any suggestion toward my second question which is <code>L / F</code> being finite (or algebraic) then <code>F_bar</code> is also the closure of <code>L</code>?</p>",
